The article is a memo from Anne Neuberger, Deputy Assistant to the President and Deputy National Security Advisor for Cyber and Emerging Technology, and Chris Inglis, National Cyber Director. It is addressed to corporate executives and business leaders and discusses the importance of protecting against malicious cyber activity during the holiday season. The memo highlights the fact that cyber criminals often take advantage of the holidays when security operations centers are understaffed. It also emphasizes the strategic risks posed by the fragility of digital infrastructure and the ever-present threat of cyber attacks. The memo provides recommendations for actions that leaders can take to reduce the risk of their organizations, including convening their leadership teams to make their organizations a harder target for criminals and implementing best practices to improve cybersecurity. The memo encourages IT and security leadership to visit the websites of CISA and the FBI for technical information and resources. It concludes by emphasizing the importance of collaboration between the U.S. government and the private sector to improve cybersecurity and wishes the readers a happy holiday season and a safe and secure New Year.